Text.Value: Tsk. I really hoped it wouldn't come to this. Poor thing.
*The corpse remains silent. You did not ask it a question.*

EditorData.logicalname: DOESN'T KNOW ANSWER - DELETE IF NOT NEEDED

Text.Value: I'm sorry. I should have helped you.
Her fate was writ the moment she fled.
Poor thing. We could have - should have - done more...
Why didn't your spell keep you safe?
She survived the druids' wrath, just to wind up like this. What a waste.
I'm sorry it had to come to this, Arabella. You were brave and fierce beyond your years.
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*

EditorData.NodeContext: Looking down at a dead child. Astarion saw her try to rob a sacred idol from some druids and respected her gumption. A touch of wistfulness, but not enough to betray his true emotions

Text.Value: *The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*

Synopsis: Arabella has been found dead. This means player refused to find her parents earlier, and she then ran off.
